result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesse James Kopp was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jesse James Kopp is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jesse James Kopp was found guilty of Contact after Domestic Abuse Arrest, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 968.075(5)(a)1.
  • Jesse James Kopp was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Jesse James Kopp was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Jesse James Kopp was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jesse James Kopp in court.  Attorney Anthony Pozorski in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Jeffrey M Ocwieja in court for Jesse James Kopp. Per agreement, defendant to plead to Counts 1-4 with 2 months jail, consecutive, costs, imposed and stayed, 2 years probation with conditions: no contact with victim, counseling, costs. Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives his rights. Defendant pleads no contest to Counts 1-4. Felony loss of rights explained. Court accepts pleas and finds defendant guilty of Counts 1-4. Counts 5-8 dismissed. State heard. Attorney Ocwieja heard. Defendant heard. Court orders probation 2 years with conditions: no contact with JO; assessments, treatment, counseling and programming as indicated by DOC; costs on Count 1; DNA.
